WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.998 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.998 --> 00:00:04.990 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.990 --> 00:00:26.480 align:middle line:90%


00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:30.116 align:middle line:84%
>> Andrew Harvey, I'm
very happy to meet you.

00:00:30.116 --> 00:00:31.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Me, to meet you.

00:00:31.460 --> 00:00:34.250 align:middle line:10%
>> You have a lot of people who
love you who are in my world

00:00:34.250 --> 00:00:35.070 align:middle line:10%
and in my path.

00:00:35.070 --> 00:00:35.870 align:middle line:10%
>> Thank you.

00:00:35.870 --> 00:00:40.670 align:middle line:10%
>> You come highly recommended,
so I love meeting you.

00:00:40.670 --> 00:00:45.680 align:middle line:84%
I want to start with a quote
that is so interesting to me.

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:48.080 align:middle line:84%
Larry Dossey who wrote
"Healing Words," one

00:00:48.080 --> 00:00:52.040 align:middle line:84%
of my favorite authors, wrote
of your book, "The Son of Man,"

00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:56.270 align:middle line:84%
this book is a grenade
tossed into the complacencies

00:00:56.270 --> 00:00:57.620 align:middle line:90%
of Christianity.

00:00:57.620 --> 00:01:02.000 align:middle line:84%
It is a radical challenge to
revision the nature of Jesus

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:03.500 align:middle line:90%
and the message he brought.

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:06.860 align:middle line:84%
It requires courage
to read this book.

00:01:06.860 --> 00:01:10.820 align:middle line:84%
But great books
always involve risk.

00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:13.520 align:middle line:84%
What did he mean when he
said it requires courage

00:01:13.520 --> 00:01:16.460 align:middle line:90%
to read this book?

00:01:16.460 --> 00:01:19.310 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I think, the vision of
Jesus that I'm trying to give

00:01:19.310 --> 00:01:22.940 align:middle line:10%
in the book is a
vision, fundamentally,

00:01:22.940 --> 00:01:25.970 align:middle line:10%
and totally different from
that, that the majority

00:01:25.970 --> 00:01:30.020 align:middle line:10%
of the Christian churches have
given people over the years.

00:01:30.020 --> 00:01:32.630 align:middle line:84%
What I'm trying to
do is to strip away

00:01:32.630 --> 00:01:35.870 align:middle line:84%
what I consider the rubbish
in the portrayal of Jesus

00:01:35.870 --> 00:01:39.650 align:middle line:84%
from the authentic historical
and mystical Jesus,

00:01:39.650 --> 00:01:45.740 align:middle line:84%
and to give the real path in its
real frightening, outrageous,

00:01:45.740 --> 00:01:48.960 align:middle line:90%
ecstatic splendor and challenge.

00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:51.600 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it takes
courage to face the real Jesus.

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:53.902 align:middle line:84%
The real Jesus, in my
opinion, is not saying,

00:01:53.902 --> 00:01:56.360 align:middle line:84%
I am the son of god and you
are just these miserable worms,

00:01:56.360 --> 00:01:59.240 align:middle line:84%
who if you pray hard enough,
will one day experience

00:01:59.240 --> 00:02:01.100 align:middle line:90%
just a taste of your divinity.

00:02:01.100 --> 00:02:04.880 align:middle line:84%
The real Jesus is saying, as
the Buddha said to humanity,

00:02:04.880 --> 00:02:07.400 align:middle line:84%
I have realized the
power of divine love,

00:02:07.400 --> 00:02:10.220 align:middle line:84%
so can you, because
I know that you can.

00:02:10.220 --> 00:02:11.820 align:middle line:90%
I am not unique.

00:02:11.820 --> 00:02:15.200 align:middle line:84%
You have this power within
you, and when you realize it,

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:18.680 align:middle line:84%
you will become like me, imbued
with the force and passion

00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:20.900 align:middle line:84%
and dynamism of the
spirit, and like me,

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:25.220 align:middle line:84%
extremely radical in the way
in which you see the world.

00:02:25.220 --> 00:02:27.553 align:middle line:84%
Because the real Jesus,
as modern scholarship

00:02:27.553 --> 00:02:29.720 align:middle line:84%
is making clear and as a
real reading of the gospels

00:02:29.720 --> 00:02:33.140 align:middle line:84%
make clear, is someone who
was a mystic revolutionary.

00:02:33.140 --> 00:02:36.680 align:middle line:84%
And being a mystic revolutionary
was a revolutionary

00:02:36.680 --> 00:02:39.570 align:middle line:84%
in every single
aspect of the world.

00:02:39.570 --> 00:02:41.910 align:middle line:84%
He was an emotional
revolutionary,

00:02:41.910 --> 00:02:45.020 align:middle line:84%
a sexual revolutionary,
an economic and political

00:02:45.020 --> 00:02:46.310 align:middle line:90%
revolutionary.

00:02:46.310 --> 00:02:50.000 align:middle line:84%
And his great challenge
to the whole human race

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:54.350 align:middle line:84%
was to bring together a vision
of divine beauty and divine

00:02:54.350 --> 00:02:57.990 align:middle line:84%
love, and a vision
of how that could

00:02:57.990 --> 00:03:01.280 align:middle line:84%
transfigure all the conditions
of real life on Earth.

00:03:01.280 --> 00:03:02.360 align:middle line:90%
And that's very scary.

00:03:02.360 --> 00:03:03.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Very scary.

00:03:03.230 --> 00:03:06.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Because it really
forces us to choose.

00:03:06.060 --> 00:03:10.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's go back to one
of the points of his being

00:03:10.700 --> 00:03:15.080 align:middle line:84%
a revolutionary that
people will really resist.

00:03:15.080 --> 00:03:17.790 align:middle line:84%
Did I hear you say he was
a sexual revolutionary?

00:03:17.790 --> 00:03:18.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:22.640 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean that Jesus indulged
in bizarre sexual practices.

00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:27.060 align:middle line:10%
I mean that Jesus, for example,
deeply venerated women.

00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:30.320 align:middle line:10%
If you think of all the
great teachers of humanity,

00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:32.820 align:middle line:10%
they all have, of course,
compassion towards men,

00:03:32.820 --> 00:03:35.570 align:middle line:10%
particularly the male
teachers, but none of them

00:03:35.570 --> 00:03:38.300 align:middle line:10%
honored and venerated women
with the depth of tenderness

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:39.680 align:middle line:10%
that Jesus did.

00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:42.110 align:middle line:84%
Jesus-- perhaps Jesus's
deepest disciple

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:43.790 align:middle line:84%
we discovered from
the gnostic gospels

00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:47.180 align:middle line:84%
was not the ones that have
been traditionally associated

00:03:47.180 --> 00:03:48.620 align:middle line:90%
with him, but Mary Magdalene.

00:03:48.620 --> 00:03:49.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, indeed.

00:03:49.610 --> 00:03:52.580 align:middle line:84%
>> And perhaps the woman
that he appeared to after his

00:03:52.580 --> 00:03:55.340 align:middle line:84%
Resurrection, the first person
to see him resurrected was

00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:56.170 align:middle line:90%
a woman.

00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:57.800 align:middle line:84%
He gave some of his
deepest teachings

00:03:57.800 --> 00:04:01.400 align:middle line:84%
to women, Phoenician
women in the gospel.

00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:04.250 align:middle line:84%
And he gave a very
profound teaching

00:04:04.250 --> 00:04:06.560 align:middle line:84%
about adultery and
about sexuality

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:09.290 align:middle line:90%
to the woman taken in adultery.

00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:11.480 align:middle line:84%
So Jesus was saying in
all of these things,

00:04:11.480 --> 00:04:14.270 align:middle line:84%
I think, the
patriarchal denigration

00:04:14.270 --> 00:04:16.820 align:middle line:84%
of the feminine, the patriarchal
humiliation of women,

00:04:16.820 --> 00:04:20.300 align:middle line:84%
and of all the associate
virtues associated with women

00:04:20.300 --> 00:04:24.650 align:middle line:84%
is a disgrace and a tremendous
defeat of the spirit.

00:04:24.650 --> 00:04:27.860 align:middle line:84%
And that true divine love
embraces the masculine

00:04:27.860 --> 00:04:29.310 align:middle line:90%
and feminine.

00:04:29.310 --> 00:04:31.760 align:middle line:84%
And that is a very
revolutionary remark,

00:04:31.760 --> 00:04:33.350 align:middle line:84%
and a very
revolutionary position,

00:04:33.350 --> 00:04:35.143 align:middle line:84%
which we still
haven't incarnated.

00:04:35.143 --> 00:04:36.560 align:middle line:84%
Look at the way
women are treated.

00:04:36.560 --> 00:04:39.870 align:middle line:84%
Look at way the feminine is
still derided and humiliated.

00:04:39.870 --> 00:04:45.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Well look at the way so many
leaders of so many Christian

00:04:45.530 --> 00:04:50.030 align:middle line:84%
churches would not think
in terms of Jesus as having

00:04:50.030 --> 00:04:52.150 align:middle line:84%
a feminine energy as well
as a masculine energy.

00:04:52.150 --> 00:04:54.020 align:middle line:90%
>> This is madness.

00:04:54.020 --> 00:04:58.370 align:middle line:84%
Because if there is
anyone who has incarnated

00:04:58.370 --> 00:05:02.840 align:middle line:84%
the aspect of the motherhood of
God more intensely than Jesus,

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:05.600 align:middle line:90%
I do not know him or her.

00:05:05.600 --> 00:05:08.430 align:middle line:84%
When I went to Israel, I
had an amazing experience.

00:05:08.430 --> 00:05:11.840 align:middle line:84%
I went to the place, [? Taka, ?]
where Jesus actually gave,

00:05:11.840 --> 00:05:14.240 align:middle line:84%
it said, the Sermon
on the Mount.

00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:16.550 align:middle line:84%
And I stood in that chapel
with the Latin Beatitudes

00:05:16.550 --> 00:05:18.967 align:middle line:84%
all around me and I sang the
Beatitudes in Latin to myself

00:05:18.967 --> 00:05:23.960 align:middle line:84%
and I gazed out at the landscape
that he had spoken to and from.

00:05:23.960 --> 00:05:26.390 align:middle line:84%
And at that moment, it
really did strike me

00:05:26.390 --> 00:05:29.210 align:middle line:84%
with a force of lightning, the
day before I had been in Sinai,

00:05:29.210 --> 00:05:32.850 align:middle line:84%
and Sinai is striated
and violent and very,

00:05:32.850 --> 00:05:33.650 align:middle line:90%
very vertical.

00:05:33.650 --> 00:05:35.775 align:middle line:84%
It's very much the place
where you would experience

00:05:35.775 --> 00:05:37.550 align:middle line:90%
God as total holiness.

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:40.220 align:middle line:84%
The landscape that he
gave the Beatitudes in

00:05:40.220 --> 00:05:43.250 align:middle line:84%
is a landscape of tremendous
maternal sweetness,

00:05:43.250 --> 00:05:45.120 align:middle line:84%
of hills rolling down
to this blue sea.

00:05:45.120 --> 00:05:45.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Interesting.

00:05:45.920 --> 00:05:48.950 align:middle line:84%
>> And at that moment I
understood that the Beatitudes

00:05:48.950 --> 00:05:51.240 align:middle line:84%
themselves are celebrating
the feminine virtues.

00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:52.040 align:middle line:90%
What did they say?

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:53.000 align:middle line:90%
Blessed are the meek.

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:54.363 align:middle line:90%
Blessed are the tender.

00:05:54.363 --> 00:05:55.280 align:middle line:90%
Blessed is the gentle.

00:05:55.280 --> 00:05:56.800 align:middle line:90%
Blessed are those who nourish.

00:05:56.800 --> 00:05:58.550 align:middle line:84%
And if you read them
in the Aramaic, which

00:05:58.550 --> 00:06:00.920 align:middle line:84%
is what I've tried to
do and tried to explore,

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:04.880 align:middle line:84%
then you realize just how
profoundly Jesus is celebrating

00:06:04.880 --> 00:06:07.250 align:middle line:84%
the feminine side of God,
the maternal side of God,

00:06:07.250 --> 00:06:09.590 align:middle line:84%
the tender side of God,
the sensitive side of God,

00:06:09.590 --> 00:06:11.180 align:middle line:90%
the nourishing side of God.

00:06:11.180 --> 00:06:14.270 align:middle line:84%
And the church has failed to
incarnate the Christ energy

00:06:14.270 --> 00:06:17.630 align:middle line:84%
because it has simply ignored
or humiliated this side.

00:06:17.630 --> 00:06:21.840 align:middle line:84%
It amounts to a crucifixion of
the real Christ consciousness.

00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:24.360 align:middle line:84%
And it is reason
why it has never

00:06:24.360 --> 00:06:28.380 align:middle line:84%
been really taken over
history as it was meant to do.

00:06:28.380 --> 00:06:30.660 align:middle line:84%
>> You're speaking of the
Beatitudes reminds me that--

00:06:30.660 --> 00:06:33.310 align:middle line:84%
let me see if I can
remember it correctly.

00:06:33.310 --> 00:06:37.020 align:middle line:84%
Your book begins with one of
the Beatitudes, I believe.

00:06:37.020 --> 00:06:40.960 align:middle line:84%
Only he who is pure
of heart will see God.

00:06:40.960 --> 00:06:42.460 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that a Beatitude
from Matthew?

00:06:42.460 --> 00:06:43.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, it is.

00:06:43.110 --> 00:06:44.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Why did you begin with that?

00:06:44.460 --> 00:06:47.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, because it's
been my experience,

00:06:47.320 --> 00:06:49.780 align:middle line:84%
as it is of every mystic
of every tradition,

00:06:49.780 --> 00:06:52.500 align:middle line:84%
that there is a seed of God
consciousness in each of us

00:06:52.500 --> 00:06:56.310 align:middle line:84%
and if you purify the heart
by meditation and by prayer

00:06:56.310 --> 00:06:59.730 align:middle line:84%
and by serving others, slowly
you come to realize that God is

00:06:59.730 --> 00:07:02.610 align:middle line:84%
shining in the heart, the
divine is shining in the heart,

00:07:02.610 --> 00:07:05.820 align:middle line:84%
and the whole world is
shining in the divine light

00:07:05.820 --> 00:07:07.120 align:middle line:90%
of the heart.

00:07:07.120 --> 00:07:10.560 align:middle line:84%
And you can only do
that if you undergo

00:07:10.560 --> 00:07:12.000 align:middle line:90%
the necessary purifications.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.050 align:middle line:84%
You have to come to understand
the darkness of your full self.

00:07:16.050 --> 00:07:18.600 align:middle line:84%
You have to really
aspire to be one

00:07:18.600 --> 00:07:21.060 align:middle line:90%
with the beloved, the divine.

00:07:21.060 --> 00:07:23.010 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
really train yourself

00:07:23.010 --> 00:07:26.730 align:middle line:84%
to concentrate on the truths
of divine relationship.

00:07:26.730 --> 00:07:29.430 align:middle line:84%
If you do, if you attain
that purity of heart,

00:07:29.430 --> 00:07:31.170 align:middle line:90%
you will see God.

00:07:31.170 --> 00:07:33.210 align:middle line:90%
You won't just believe in God.

00:07:33.210 --> 00:07:35.010 align:middle line:84%
You won't just have
faith that God exists.

00:07:35.010 --> 00:07:36.605 align:middle line:90%
You will see God.

00:07:36.605 --> 00:07:38.730 align:middle line:84%
And for the last 10 years
through the grace of God,

00:07:38.730 --> 00:07:40.710 align:middle line:90%
I have been seeing God.

00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:43.410 align:middle line:84%
And I would wish every
single human being

00:07:43.410 --> 00:07:46.530 align:middle line:84%
to have that experience
because it's an experience that

00:07:46.530 --> 00:07:51.775 align:middle line:84%
changes totally what we know
of life [INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:07:51.775 --> 00:07:52.575 align:middle line:90%
as the feast.

00:07:52.575 --> 00:07:53.880 align:middle line:90%
>> What a gift.

00:07:53.880 --> 00:07:57.460 align:middle line:84%
What a marvelous opportunity
for you to be able to see God.

00:07:57.460 --> 00:07:58.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Well I think everybody can.

00:07:58.710 --> 00:07:59.760 align:middle line:90%
That's what I know.

00:07:59.760 --> 00:08:00.570 align:middle line:90%
And that's what Jesus knew.

00:08:00.570 --> 00:08:01.350 align:middle line:90%
That's what the Buddha knew.

00:08:01.350 --> 00:08:02.280 align:middle line:84%
That's what Roman
Christian knew.

00:08:02.280 --> 00:08:04.380 align:middle line:84%
That's what everybody
who sees God knows

00:08:04.380 --> 00:08:07.020 align:middle line:84%
is that everyone could see
God if they loved enough,

00:08:07.020 --> 00:08:09.030 align:middle line:84%
if they gave enough, if
they sacrificed enough,

00:08:09.030 --> 00:08:11.850 align:middle line:84%
if they prayed enough, if
they believed enough, if they

00:08:11.850 --> 00:08:14.250 align:middle line:90%
sacrificed their self enough.

00:08:14.250 --> 00:08:15.530 align:middle line:90%
It's not a unique gift.

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:17.730 align:middle line:84%
There are many
people who see God--

00:08:17.730 --> 00:08:18.870 align:middle line:90%
many.

00:08:18.870 --> 00:08:22.020 align:middle line:84%
And the more I see
of God, the more

00:08:22.020 --> 00:08:24.990 align:middle line:84%
I realized that God is
blazing all around us.

00:08:24.990 --> 00:08:26.070 align:middle line:90%
We're just blind.

00:08:26.070 --> 00:08:30.300 align:middle line:10%
>> Well now I must say,
I can feel his presence.

00:08:30.300 --> 00:08:32.379 align:middle line:10%
I feel a presence--

00:08:32.379 --> 00:08:33.179 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:36.553 align:middle line:84%
>> --of God around me at
times, not all the time.

00:08:36.553 --> 00:08:38.220 align:middle line:84%
But I can't say that
I've ever seen him.

00:08:38.220 --> 00:08:40.200 align:middle line:90%
What is it like?

00:08:40.200 --> 00:08:43.380 align:middle line:84%
Is it like an apparition or do
you see him in someone else?

00:08:43.380 --> 00:08:47.100 align:middle line:84%
>> You see him in everything
and as everything.

00:08:47.100 --> 00:08:49.320 align:middle line:84%
The world becomes
a place where God

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:53.790 align:middle line:84%
is experienced as manifesting in
every flower, in every banana,

00:08:53.790 --> 00:08:57.420 align:middle line:84%
in every child, in every
eye-- your eyes now.

00:08:57.420 --> 00:09:00.690 align:middle line:84%
The whole experience
is one of the divine

00:09:00.690 --> 00:09:03.750 align:middle line:84%
in you savoring and
celebrating and honoring

00:09:03.750 --> 00:09:06.450 align:middle line:84%
the divine in everyone
else and everything

00:09:06.450 --> 00:09:08.370 align:middle line:90%
else so that it becomes--

00:09:08.370 --> 00:09:09.810 align:middle line:84%
it's impossible
to put into words.

00:09:09.810 --> 00:09:12.760 align:middle line:84%
The greatest mystical poets
have tried and failed.

00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:15.120 align:middle line:84%
But what Rumi said in one
of his late poems, I think,

00:09:15.120 --> 00:09:16.380 align:middle line:90%
is really powerful.

00:09:16.380 --> 00:09:20.610 align:middle line:84%
He says, "I see the waters of
magnificent streaming always,

00:09:20.610 --> 00:09:22.650 align:middle line:84%
and the whole of
heaven and earth

00:09:22.650 --> 00:09:25.440 align:middle line:84%
reveals itself as
the Resurrection,

00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:28.140 align:middle line:84%
as the place where the
divine is dancing."

00:09:28.140 --> 00:09:32.130 align:middle line:10%
And that is not poetry actually,
that is a living experience.

00:09:32.130 --> 00:09:34.860 align:middle line:84%
And I'm convinced that many,
many more people could have it

00:09:34.860 --> 00:09:36.480 align:middle line:90%
than think they could have it.

00:09:36.480 --> 00:09:39.140 align:middle line:84%
Because we've really
said, oh, there

00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:41.640 align:middle line:84%
are these great mystics who
have this extraordinary spirits,

00:09:41.640 --> 00:09:44.880 align:middle line:84%
but we're just poor human beings
crawling around in our lives.

00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:47.383 align:middle line:84%
And they have the experience,
and we get support

00:09:47.383 --> 00:09:48.300 align:middle line:90%
from their experience.

00:09:48.300 --> 00:09:49.950 align:middle line:90%
This is nonsense.

00:09:49.950 --> 00:09:52.110 align:middle line:84%
Everybody can have
this experience.

00:09:52.110 --> 00:09:55.560 align:middle line:84%
To have this experience
is why we are here.

00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:57.330 align:middle line:84%
We are the children
of the father mother.

00:09:57.330 --> 00:09:58.950 align:middle line:90%
We have the power within us.

00:09:58.950 --> 00:10:02.790 align:middle line:84%
What we need are the simple
techniques of meditation,

